{
    "ai-tha-ap109:0.1_0": "Therāpadāna",
    "ai-tha-ap109:0.2_0": "Bhikkhadāyivagga",
    "ai-tha-ap109:0.3_0": "7. Naḷamāliyattheraapadāna",
    "ai-tha-ap109:1.1_0": "“Padumuttara, the Buddha Padumuttara,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:1.2_0": "poised one in the world.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:1.3_0": "As he was sitting on the seat spread out.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:1.4_0": "where would anger come from?",
    "ai-tha-ap109:2.1_0": "I took a garland of flowers,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:2.2_0": "I tied the seed",
    "ai-tha-ap109:2.3_0": "I worship the Buddha,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:2.4_0": "the poised one, the perfected one;",
    "ai-tha-ap109:3.1_0": "The one received it all.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:3.2_0": "the seed in the world",
    "ai-tha-ap109:3.3_0": "Knowing my thoughts,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:3.4_0": "spoke this verse:",
    "ai-tha-ap109:4.1_0": "‘My body is tied up.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:4.2_0": "no fever is found in them.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:4.3_0": "So too, in the threefold",
    "ai-tha-ap109:4.4_0": "your mind is freed!”",
    "ai-tha-ap109:5.1_0": "all the gods,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:5.2_0": "Whatever foes in the forest is lived,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:5.3_0": "there shall be the Buddha’s words.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:5.4_0": "Circling down, discontent,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:6.1_0": "while sitting,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:6.2_0": "at the fore of the gods.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:6.3_0": "By giving food and drink",
    "ai-tha-ap109:6.4_0": "the verses on these verses:",
    "ai-tha-ap109:7.1_0": "“This is the source of this seed!",
    "ai-tha-ap109:7.2_0": "Citta and Pajjīsa",
    "ai-tha-ap109:7.3_0": "As a well-being mind:",
    "ai-tha-ap109:7.4_0": "a wheel-turning monarch.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:8.1_0": "Through the remainder of that deed,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:8.2_0": "you’ve been accused like a tortoise:",
    "ai-tha-ap109:8.3_0": "not by name, not by the boat.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:8.4_0": "wheel will be rolling.’",
    "ai-tha-ap109:9.1_0": "This is the reason why",
    "ai-tha-ap109:9.2_0": "and right bodily—",
    "ai-tha-ap109:9.3_0": "A hundred thousand aeons",
    "ai-tha-ap109:9.4_0": "so he does not.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:10.1_0": "The thirty-two thousand chiefs",
    "ai-tha-ap109:10.2_0": "Eight years after the thirty-eights.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:10.3_0": "Eleven thousand",
    "ai-tha-ap109:10.4_0": "Eight binding creeper leaves,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:11.1_0": "the four analytical knowledges,",
    "ai-tha-ap109:11.2_0": "... “I’ll sleep ...”",
    "ai-tha-ap109:11.3_0": "and fulfilled the Buddha’s instructions.”",
    "ai-tha-ap109:12.1_0": "That is how these verses were recited by the senior venerable Nandā.",
    "ai-tha-ap109:13.1_0": "for the sake of the Elder Nun Nandā",
    "ai-tha-ap109:13.2_0": "Seventh section for recitation is finished."
}